# Typecheck Discipline

- Run `npm run typecheck` after relevant code changes in TypeScript or shared runtime paths.
- Resolve introduced type errors before finishing the task.
- If a change intentionally alters types, update affected annotations and call sites in the same task.
- Prefer precise types over `any`; use narrowing and explicit unions when needed.
- Keep type checks fast and local to project scripts.

## Example

```ts
type Status = "idle" | "loading" | "done";

function renderStatus(status: Status): string {
  if (status === "loading") return "Loading...";
  if (status === "done") return "Done";
  return "Idle";
}
```
